properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 2:37AM CST until January 11 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTER WEATHER WILL IMPACT TRAVEL THIS WEEKEND...

.Another round of snow will arrive late this afternoon and early
evening, bringing snowfall totals of 2 to 6 inches, heaviest
along the lakeshore. Along with the snowfall, considerable blowing
and drifting snow will occur, especially from the Fox Valley to
the lakeshore counties. The worst conditions will occur along the
lakeshore areas, where the highest snowfall totals are expected,
and northeast winds will gust to 35 to 40 mph. Travel conditions
will be significantly impacted.

The strong northeast winds will also result in increased
potential for lakeshore flooding, shoreline erosion, and ice
shoves on the bay and Lake Winnebago.

* WHAT...For the Winter Storm Warning, heavy snow and blowing snow
expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6 inches. Winds
gusting as high as 40 mph. For the Winter Weather Advisory, snow
and blowing snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to one
inch. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Manitowoc County.

* WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, from 3 PM this afternoon
to 6 AM CST Sunday. For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 6
AM CST early this morning.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Areas of blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds could bring
down tree branches, resulting in localized power outages.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
